Quickly probe a document for shape signals (format, page count, has-text, likely-scanned, has-tables, has-encryption, font resolution counts) without doing a full extraction.

Body lands in. The variant exists here as a stub so the subcommand tree parses correctly.

Usage: udoc inspect [OPTIONS] <FILE>

Arguments:
  <FILE>
          Input document

Options:
      --full
          Force a complete scan instead of the default sampled mode. Sampled mode looks at 5 pages spread across the document; `--full` walks every page

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
